    <h3>Where Amberwood scores well</h3>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>GLS pipeline (5&#9733;).</strong> Eight confirmed or reserve GLS plots within a 2&nbsp;km radius. That&rsquo;s a structural tailwind: every successful future land bid rebenchmarks the entry pricing of today&rsquo;s launches upward.</li>
      <li><strong>School effect (5&#9733;).</strong> A 1&nbsp;km MGS catchment is one of the most evergreen demand pools in Singapore property &mdash; it cycles with the school calendar, not the property cycle.</li>
      <li><strong>Rental yield (5&#9733;).</strong> Projected ~3.1% gross yield is meaningfully above the CCR average, which is rare for D10. For yield-focused buyers, that&rsquo;s the headline number.</li>
      <li><strong>Remaining tenure (5&#9733;).</strong> A fresh 99-year lease (~98 balance at handover) means zero immediate lease-decay drag. Exit windows stay clean for 20+ years.</li>
      <li><strong>Growth hotspot (5&#9733;).</strong> The site is 0.8&nbsp;km from the Turf City transformation &mdash; one of the largest planned mixed-use redevelopments in the western corridor. Infrastructure spend in that direction will keep flowing.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Where it doesn&rsquo;t</h3>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>MRT walk (2&#9733;).</strong> A 13-minute walk to King Albert Park MRT is acceptable for many residents (especially with feeder buses or a car), but it&rsquo;s not the sub-5-minute walk that maximises rentability with the tightest tenant pool. Discount the project accordingly if MRT-walkability is your top tenant filter.</li>
      <li><strong>MOP / upgrader cluster (1&#9733;).</strong> There are <em>no</em> HDB or BTO units within 2&nbsp;km expected to reach MOP in the next 10 years. That removes a key source of short-term, walk-in upgrader demand. For long-term holders this barely matters &mdash; for someone hoping to flip in 5 years, it matters a lot.</li>
    </ul>

