    <h2>Who is Amberwood at Holland actually for?</h2>

    <p>Strip away the launch noise and the buyer profile resolves quite cleanly:</p>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Families with school priorities</strong> who want to lock down the MGS catchment with a fresh 99-year lease, not an ageing freehold further out.</li>
      <li><strong>Yield-focused investors</strong> who want CCR exposure but won&rsquo;t accept the typical 2&ndash;2.5% D10 yield ceiling.</li>
      <li><strong>Long-horizon capital growth buyers</strong> who are positioning ahead of the Turf City + Holland Plain + CRL2032 catalyst chain rather than next quarter&rsquo;s rebound.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>It&rsquo;s a weaker fit if you need an under-5-minute MRT walk for tenant filtering, or if your underwriting assumes a quick 3&ndash;5 year flip into a wave of nearby HDB upgraders &mdash; that demand pool isn&rsquo;t there in this micro-market.</p>

    <p>Either way, the responsible next step is to <em>see the data before you see the showflat</em>. Download the PrimeKey Report above, line it up against any other D10 shortlist you&rsquo;re considering, and decide on facts &mdash; not on the brochure&rsquo;s rendering quality.</p>

